      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Reaching your limit or considering letting go can seem selfish, but it might also be an act of self-preservation. You are human, and your well-being is important too. Remember, taking care of yourself is not selfish; it's necessary. There is a kind of dignity in acknowledging when you've reached your limit, and it's perfectly okay to seek a way that might bring peace for you and your family. But before making any drastic decisions, consider exploring all possible options for support and help.",
